{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in lentils and water. Set aside to soak for 1 hour.","Place cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Cut eggplants into slices (½ in.) and place into Varoma dish. Make sure that some holes in the Varoma dish remain unobstructed for steam to escape. Set Varoma aside.","Place oil, onions, garlic and bell pepper into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add tomatoes and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add wine, oregano, ginger, salt and pepper. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>20 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1<b>. Set Varoma aside.","Add drained red lentils and cook <b>8 min\/212°F\/\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 400°F and grease a baking dish (approx. 12 in. x 8 in. x 2 in.). Arrange eggplant slices in baking dish and cover with lentil mixture. No need to clean mixing bowl.","Place butter, milk and flour into mixing bowl and cook <b>8 min\/195°F\/speed 4<b>.","Add 2 oz reserved grated cheese and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Cover lentil layer with sauce and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese. Bake moussaka for 30 minutes (400°F). Cut moussaka into squares and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["7 oz red split lentils","18 oz water","4 ½ oz Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces","14 oz eggplants","2 oz olive oil","7 oz yellow onions, halved","3 garlic cloves","1 bell pepper, green or red, cut into pieces (approx. 5.5 oz)","1 can tomatoes, (approx. 15 oz), undrained","4 oz red wine","1 tbsp dried oregano","1 tsp ground ginger","1 - 2 tsp salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper","1 ½ oz unsalted butter, plus extra to grease","18 oz whole milk","1 ½ oz all-purpose flour"]}],"id":"r91277","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-kvi_YOErR-A\/XZVRlxvjUEI\/AAAAAAAAdQg\/JYokg5FxpA0RHQA6THigfFE0BsrJyNuOQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_s-MCs0Jtl7Ysfl1U.png","title":"Lentil Moussaka","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"21 g","fat":"28 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"33 g","calories":"2064 kJ \/ 492 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rectangular baking dish (approx. 12 in. x 8 in. x 2 in.), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Instead of soaked red lentils you can use pre-cooked brown lentils."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h 20m","6 portions"]}